attributes.label: Start - Her one day trip to Misora
attributes.characterDialogue: My weekend was unfortunately not that great. I went on a one-day trip to Misora. With my <style="Link">Annoying Husband</style>. Just kidding, he is great.  You wonder why it was bad? So, we stayed at this very ugly and chaotic <style="Link">Hotel</style>. And honestly, I don't know about you but I absolutely hate chaos. On top of that, we didn't get any food there, so we had to eat in the Local <style="Link">Bad Restaurants</style>.

attributes.label: Rejected from Hotel
attributes.characterDialogue: The original hotel they wanted to stay at rejected them

attributes.label: Restaurant "Above the skies"
attributes.characterDialogue: Hmmm "Above the Clouds" Now that you mention it, That reminds me of this one Restaurant in Misora called "Above the skies". Their name is weird, because when I was there they only served sandwiches. Like why call yourself "Above the skies" then, how am I suppposed to understand what they are selling?

attributes.label: City Hall
attributes.characterDialogue: They were here

attributes.label: The Viewing Platform
attributes.characterDialogue: She was at one of the Viewing Platform. The view was actually quite nice.

attributes.label: Shark Pound
attributes.characterDialogue: Shark Pund, Duckling Lake, Weird City Names, Beaches

attributes.label: Coffee Shop
attributes.characterDialogue: Right, the Coffe Shop. You know, I know how to make good coffee, because I like getting up <style="Link">Early</style> at home and watching all the <style="Link">Hot Boys</style> do their Workouts in the Park, heh. From the balcony though, I don't really like <style="Link">Greenery</style>. So yeah I know what good coffee is, but this mass production, eh. <style="Link">Quality</style> over Quantity, i always say.

attributes.label: Greenery
attributes.characterDialogue: There was a lot of greenery in the city

attributes.label: Harbor
attributes.characterDialogue: They avoided the Harbor, because she hates the stinking fish

attributes.label: Fish & Crab Market
attributes.characterDialogue: They went past the Fish & Crab Market and she hated the smell

attributes.label: Surfing Club
attributes.characterDialogue: She liked seeing hot surfers guys on the beach. There where really hot once, close to the Surfing Club in Misora. Her husband was mad at her for whistling but she doesnt understand why

attributes.label: Horrible Trip
attributes.characterDialogue: To sum it all up, the trip was horrible! First I got <style="Link">Sick</style> from the terrible food, combined with a boat ride with one of the most incompetent captains I have ever met. Even my husband could do that better. On top of that, I <style="Link">Couldn't Sleep</style> all night! But not because of my mind! I meditate a lot and therefore live in perfect Edu..Eudaimoni...! Oh and then there was all the <style="Link">Discrimination</style>! No one respects a successful Lady. Sometimes I think I'm too kind to people...

attributes.label: Restricted Parks
attributes.characterDialogue: All of those restricted areas in Misora at the City Hall and at the Hotel were so annoying!  They were rejected both times from entering. Unbelievable! She isn't one of those poor people and shouldnt't be treated like that and even after she explained them for 10 minutes that they should still be permitted to enter, they still didn't let them in. Then they had to walk all the way around.

attributes.label: No meal plans in the Hotel
attributes.characterDialogue: It is unbelievable that the Hotels in Misora don't offer any food, that is a total scam. And being forced to eat all that horrible food at those restaurants just further ruined her trip

attributes.label: Special Services for Cozy Camping
attributes.characterDialogue: Dolphin Tour, Annoying Children, Mount Doom, Cozy Camping Gondolas

attributes.label: Noise
attributes.characterDialogue: Ohh, the Noise. I have very sensitive ears, and all those loud <style="Link">Children</style> there and my <style="Link">Husband</style> on top of that. That was too much. I felt so <style="Link">Discriminated</style>! If you were as unique of a person as I am, you would understand what I am talking about. Everything is always made for the average people. It's so unfair, just a <style="Link">Horrible Experience</style>.

attributes.label: Bought Gem Jewelry
attributes.characterDialogue: She brought home some expensive Jewellery, like a pearl necklace and an emerald bracelet. When she bought it her husband said she doesn't need it but she believes otherwise

attributes.label: Not needingPublic Transport
attributes.characterDialogue: Because she is a lady of class, she doesnt need to use public transport, she only makes exceptions where it is absolutely nessesary, like in Misora, when they took the bus. Good thing she wasn't pickpocketed

attributes.label: Style Boutiques
attributes.characterDialogue: They went to a lot of different Style Boutiques

attributes.label: Busses
attributes.characterDialogue: They went on a bus in the morning. The busses were  also with an audio guide, teeling them about the different buildings they passed

attributes.label: Bad Local Restaurants
attributes.characterDialogue: Oh yeah, the Restaurants really turned it into a <style="Link">Horrible Trip</style>! But still, we wanted to give them a chance, hah. I remember a <style="Link">Coffee Shop</style> a <style="Link">Seafood Restaurant</style> another <style="Link">Restaurant</style> before returning back to the Hotel, and this other one in the mountains. But yeah, anyways have I told you about the <style="Link">Hot Boys</style>?

attributes.label: Start in the Web
attributes.characterDialogue: null

attributes.label: Ocean annoying
attributes.characterDialogue: Annoying Children, Boat Tour, Noise

attributes.label: Galleries
attributes.characterDialogue: They first wanted to go inside a Gallery in morning but it wasn't open yet, So they headed to another

attributes.label: The great view
attributes.characterDialogue: The view from the Top was just crazy good, you could see so much of the city

attributes.label: Boat Tours
attributes.characterDialogue: There are a lot of Boat Tours, but the only thing she got out of it was getting seasick. At least She didn't throw up like my husband

attributes.label: All  those small walkways
attributes.characterDialogue: You can see all the hiking paths from the viewign platform, the gondolas and they are all on mount doom

attributes.label: a fan of architecture
attributes.characterDialogue: Architecture is one of her hobbies. Misora was supposed to have beatiful architecture, but really it was not that much. The churches were definitly impressive but that is always the case for religious sites. The City hall was not that impressive. Quite the scam actually

attributes.label: Stores
attributes.characterDialogue: They were in a bunch of "different" premium stores

attributes.label: Beaches
attributes.characterDialogue: They traveled along the beach because they wanted to get to a gallery at the end

attributes.label: Seafood Restaurant
attributes.characterDialogue: We went to this seafood restaurant near the beach, together. It was very expensive, which wasn't the problem because I mean, I have the <style="Link">Money</style>. But the food...just the thought of eating slimy <style="Link">Ocean Animals</style> is so disgusting. But you know, there were <style="Link">No meal</style> plans in the Hotel, so we had to eat the local junk.

attributes.label: The Cathedral on the hill
attributes.characterDialogue: It looked magnificent.  They wanted to go but the were really hungry and wanted to eat something

attributes.label: Hurting Feet
attributes.characterDialogue: From all that Hiking her feet hurt so much. An important lady like her shouldnt have to worry about something like that. One of the many reasons why this trip was horrible

attributes.label: Hot Boys
attributes.characterDialogue: Hmm, that reminds me of the Hot Boys in Misora. That's one good thing about <style="Link">The scorching sun</style>. Especially the ones from the <style="Link">Surfing Club</style>, in their swimming shorts.  They all looked like they were modeling for the local <style="Link">Style Boutiques</style>. Hmm, I love vacations.

attributes.label: Climate Activists
attributes.characterDialogue: She hates those climate activist always spraying tomato sauce over rare items. So that's what the young generation is all about now? Riding busses and destroying rare items?

attributes.label: Hotel: The Pearl
attributes.characterDialogue: She isn't a fan of the Hotel "The Pearl" anymore, first they deny them the stay and then they didn't even let them pass through.  They had to take such a long path around the property to get where she wanted to go

attributes.label: Why it's called Platypus Beach
attributes.characterDialogue: Weird City Names, Names of the boat tour, The scourchin sun

attributes.label: Getting up early
attributes.characterDialogue: I ALWAYS get up early. Especially on vacation! That way I am able to see as much as possible! But sleeping with all that <style="Link">Noise</style> in Misora, was not easy anyways. So even my husband got up early and we managed to take the first <style="Link">Bus</style> towards the city center.

attributes.label: Cozy Camping Gondola
attributes.characterDialogue: Gondolas, Discrimination, Hotel Cozy Camping

attributes.label: Names of the shopping district streets
attributes.characterDialogue: Why its called Platypus Beach, Coffee Shop, Stores

attributes.label: Duckling Lake
attributes.characterDialogue: Special Services for Cozy Camping, Why its called platypus beach, weird city names, hot boys

attributes.label: No sleep
attributes.characterDialogue: Yeah, I got no sleep there! The hotel we got <style="Link">Rejected</style> from would have been more to my standards! My body is a temple, and you don't place a temple on cheap foam matrasses! But besides that, I usually <style="Link">Wake Up</style>early and also<style="Link">Work Hard</style> and into the Night, and because of that I am simply not used to this mode of doing nothing, you know. Oh don't look at me like that. That is what it takes if you want to be as successful as me, my dear.

attributes.label: Gondolas
attributes.characterDialogue: She took a gondola down the mountain

attributes.label: Quality over Quantity
attributes.characterDialogue: She believes in "Quality over Quantity". She strives to stay a Lady of Class and appreciates True Beauty. Because of this she actually developed quite the Fine Taste, which not everyone can please. Especially not those awful restaurants, she was at in Misora.

attributes.label: Sickness
attributes.characterDialogue: Ocean annoying, Bad local restaurants, the scorching sun

attributes.label: Hiking / Mountain
attributes.characterDialogue: When she went up the Mount Doom it was very annoying for her

attributes.label: Restaurant in the Evening
attributes.characterDialogue: In the evening, I went to this small Pizzeria, near our Hotel. Thought I could get some normal food there since there are <style="Link">No Meal</style> plans in the Hotel hah. And after the hike, I was very hungry. But it wasn't really a place for a <style="Link">Classy Lady</style> like me. It was very simple and bland but at least not as bad as the <style="Link">Seafood Restaurant</style>.

attributes.label: The scorching sun
attributes.characterDialogue: Oh, don't remind me. The sun was horrible. That much UV exposure is not good for my <style="Link">Beauty</style>. But it does help with <style="Link">Getting Up</style> Early, even though I usually get up before the sun rises.  But with all the heat that it brought, I wish we would have passed by the <style="Link">Ducking Lake</style>. I heard it is wonderful for bathing.

attributes.label: Classy Lady
attributes.characterDialogue: She is so special and perfect, and people should respect that, but instead the whole city didnt show any respect

attributes.label: Her interest in vintage cars
attributes.characterDialogue: She loves cars especially vintage ones, she's disappointed of Misora. She heard of a car colletion but they couldnt find one.

attributes.label: Names of the Boat Tours
attributes.characterDialogue: Plankton Zoo, Names of the shopping district streets, Boat Tours

attributes.label: Discrimination
attributes.characterDialogue: On the Trip she was discriminated against for being a woman, because she wasn't able to access certain attractions

attributes.label: Dolphin Tour
attributes.characterDialogue: The Dolphin Tour is a special <style="Link">Boat Tour</style> only for guest of <style="Link">Cozy Camping</style>. It leads directly to <style="Link">Duckling Lake</style>. She finds the <style="Link">naming conventions</style>

attributes.label: Annoying Husband
attributes.characterDialogue: She talks about her and her husband going on the trip together, but starts complaining about him immediately

attributes.label: Hotel
attributes.characterDialogue:
Our day started with checking in to our small and simple Hotel. Im so glad that we took the <style="Link">Plane</style> and not the Train like my goofy husband suggested. He cares about the environment, but I'm more of a luxury person. 
However, he turned me so eco-friendly in Misora, haha. Right after we got to the Hotel  we took the local<style="Link">Bus</style>  to get to a <style="Link">Coffee Shop</style>.

attributes.label: Too much walking
attributes.characterDialogue: She had to walk way to much.

attributes.label: Fisherman
attributes.characterDialogue: She hates the harbor but those fisherman, she does respect.  They work hard and as you can see they are clearly very rich people since they can effort all those boats

attributes.label: Algea Bay
attributes.characterDialogue: They saw it from the distance and decided it wasn't worth going to

attributes.label: Beauty
attributes.characterDialogue: Oh, thank you for noticing. My beauty is <style="Link">all natural</style> of course. <style="Link">Appearance</style> means a lot to me. That is how others see you, and you would only want them to see the best of you am I right?  <style="Link">Shopping</style> for these looks is not always that cheap, but it is worth it!

attributes.label: Spa
attributes.characterDialogue: They were at a Spa in Misora

attributes.label: Having Disagreements with her husband
attributes.characterDialogue: From time to time there are some times instances where her husband gets angry at her for no reason, but those can be quickly resolved and would never destroy the bond they share

attributes.label: Her dress she is wearing
attributes.characterDialogue: null

attributes.label: Hotel "Cozy Camping"
attributes.characterDialogue: She is very glad she didn't stay at Cozy Camping,  They passed the Hotel and all of the Campers smelled horrible

attributes.label: The young generation
attributes.characterDialogue: Ah, this young generation... Always <style="Link">sleeping in</style>because they play <style="Link">video games</style> all day. I have a nephew, I know what I'm talking about.

attributes.label: Religious Sites
attributes.characterDialogue: She is a fan of religious sites and they actually passed one in Misora, but there was a wedding happening so she couldn't enter.

attributes.label: Poor people
attributes.characterDialogue: Poverty is a mindset, all those poor people just dont work hard enough.  They should take an example on those fisherman.  They at least work hard. She is just not meant to be around poor people. That is why she doesnt usually use the public transport

attributes.label: Holy Mario
attributes.characterDialogue: They went past this weird statue, but she couldn't get a close look at it. It's a very weird statue with a very weird name. As an appreciator of real beauty she says she can live without buying it at the statue shop

attributes.label: The stuff she brought home
attributes.characterDialogue: She brought a bunch of stuff home, her favourite piece is the dress they bought. Honestly she has bought so much stuff, she would have even bought out the museum if the stuff in there wasn't "Not for Sale"

attributes.label: Displaying Wealth
attributes.characterDialogue: Bought Gem Jewellery, Her plan for private Mansion, Money

attributes.label: a shop for statues
attributes.characterDialogue: They went to a premium souvenier shop of statues for the different memorials.  They didn't have names so she just picked the one which was prettiest, they also got a stone as a gift, which she is still confused by.

attributes.label: Video Games
attributes.characterDialogue: Oh yes video games, my nephew is always glued ot them and playing all day. I must admit, I've caught myself sneaking a few round of this racing game. Guess I'm still young at hearth after all. You know, when I heard the name "Mario" in Misora I thought I was gonna see the one from the video game, but instead it was just a boring old statue, which doesn't look like Mario at all.  They shouldn't have named it like that. It's so confusing. This city really was full of weird and confusing names.

attributes.label: City Info
attributes.characterDialogue: They didnt receive as much info about the city as they would have liked, she complains that there wasn't any info point

attributes.label: Didn't pass through a tunnel
attributes.characterDialogue: They did not pass through a tunnel

attributes.label: Her plan for a private Mansion
attributes.characterDialogue: As a fan of architecture her goal of course is to have her own private mansion and fill it with all the rare stuff she gathered. She plans to buy a second island.

attributes.label: Plankton Zoo
attributes.characterDialogue: Why its called Platypus Beach, weird City Names, Seafood restaurant

attributes.label: Museum of Modern Art
attributes.characterDialogue: They saw it, but didn't go because "You can't buy the paintings there"

attributes.label: Friedas Garden Center
attributes.characterDialogue: They passed it but didnt go, she also talk about a weird fact about it

attributes.label: House Plants
attributes.characterDialogue: She loves houseplant, especially either really big ones or really small cute one's. She can put those in her mansion.  They saw a Garden Center but didnt go at the end. One has to set priorities.

attributes.label: She works hard
attributes.characterDialogue: To become the important person she is now she needed to work hard, something which the poor people definitly dont know how to do

attributes.label: Gambling
attributes.characterDialogue: Although she would have the money for it, she would never gamble. Gambling is just a scam and she doesn't understand why some people would go as far as to gamble their saving away. Just Stop, when you already spend to much. Then they don't have to be surprised if the can't effort anything anymore. She's glad she didn't have to look at one in Misora

attributes.label: Magpie Island
attributes.characterDialogue: Yes my private Island "Magpie Island" or how I like to call it "My kingdom". It's close to Misora. I love it! That's why I went, to check out the neighborhood. There is actually a Boat Tour going to my island but I couldn't find where it started. Actually now that I think about it, I should get another!

attributes.label: Ocean Animals
attributes.characterDialogue: This city seems to really like ocean animals. "Shark Pound" "Plankton Zoo"? She thinks they are crazy. Although it makes sense, considering the live close to the beach and Harbor

attributes.label: Getting money stolen
attributes.characterDialogue: The fear of getting all her money stolen is just so stressfull on her. Getting pickpocketed is just the worse, which is why they avoided the Fish and Crab Market in Misora. Aand that is also why she founded her company, to protect the people that need their money protected.

attributes.label: Getting scammed
attributes.characterDialogue: There are Scams everywhere, like this shitty excuse of a beach called "Algea Bay" in Misora. Or all of those dirty tricks that are used in Casinos. I'm sure you can't even win anything. But the biggest scam of all time is of course the moon landing. Fake all through

attributes.label: Working hard
attributes.characterDialogue: She believes that, working hard is a thing that the young generation has forgot about. But all they say is "Uhhhhh my 10 hours of sleep weeeeeee".  They should get their shit together and take example on herself

attributes.label: She is super important
attributes.characterDialogue: She is a woman of great importance and should be discriminated against like she was in Misora. She should have access to anywhere and others should work to respect the high position she is in

attributes.label: What her company does
attributes.characterDialogue: My company? You don't know what we do? We sell the very prestige service of offering people that need it to register their company on my private island and since it is declared as it's own country, I make the rules there. Which are "Do what you want" and "Don't pay any taxes". A much better enviroment to thrive than those horrible goverments.

attributes.label: Money
attributes.characterDialogue: Having so much money and so much responsibility can bo so stressfull. But not for her, because she knows exactly where it is best invested in, her own beauty. As well as going shopping and finding the real quality products.

attributes.label: Cooling Water
attributes.characterDialogue: Yes some cooling water for that scourchin sun would have been nice. Maybe she should learn to surf at a surf club, then she can be cool and do sport at the same time. Or maybe she just becomes an ocean animal, then she can stay in the water forever.

attributes.label: Rarities
attributes.characterDialogue: She is quite the fan of collecting rarities, like rare vintage cars. When going on a trip you of course have to bring home some of those home. To do that they were at premium souvenir shop. It's a shame there were no auctions running, she would have totally bought something there.

attributes.label: Annoying Children
attributes.characterDialogue: Hotel Cozy Camping, Names of the Boat Tours, Horrible Trip

attributes.label: Mount  Doom
attributes.characterDialogue: The great view, Mount everest, Hotel Cozy Camping, Naming of the pathways

attributes.label: Weird City Names
attributes.characterDialogue: Names of the shopping district streets, Styles abroad are so unique, Plankton ZoOo

attributes.label: a beautiful dress
attributes.characterDialogue: Styles abroad are so unique, beauty, Bought Gem Jewellery

attributes.label: Owning a second Island
attributes.characterDialogue: I should definitly get myself a second island. I already have a plan. I got "My Kingdom" during an auction, so I'm going to visit the upcoming auctions and wait for my chance to strike. I can usually sniff a good deal the moment I see it. Ahhh It's gonna be so amazing having a second island to show and inspire other people of how a successfull person looks like.

attributes.label: She is all natural
attributes.characterDialogue: Though a lot of people think so, she is actually completly natural. No plastic surgeries, no Make Up. She says it's because of her regular spa visits, but it might actually be because of her age. Because she is actually very young, you see

attributes.label: She is still young
attributes.characterDialogue: The young generation, Climate Activists, Museum of Modern art

attributes.label: Ancient Statues
attributes.characterDialogue: Holy mario, Museum of Modern art

attributes.label: So many things to do
attributes.characterDialogue: She talks about all the possiblities of what young people these days can do  and how everything is changing

attributes.label: Styles abroad are so unique
attributes.characterDialogue: Stuff is so different abroad. Especially these unique fashions style in the clothing stores and the great asian massages at the spa

attributes.label: Start in the Web - She uses the service herself
attributes.characterDialogue: She uses the service herself and starts talking about her company

attributes.label: Start in the Web 2
attributes.characterDialogue: No one is willing to work these days anymore

attributes.label: Naming of the Pathways
attributes.characterDialogue: She noticed that the pathways have very weird animal names

attributes.label: Auctions
attributes.characterDialogue: She loves going to different auctions, a much better way to spend so much money, than gambling all of your money away. She espacially likes going to the one's in different galleries around the world.

attributes.label: End
attributes.characterDialogue: Mmmmmm now that I think about it, you are actually not really worth my time, <style="Link">byeeeeeeee</style>

attributes.label: Planes
attributes.characterDialogue: That's the thing, I just love being in <style="Link">Great Hights</style>. But to get to Misora, we had to be <style="Link"> Awake Early </style> just for the Plane to be late once again. That's the problem with planes. Always late! Even worse than <style="Link">Public Transport</style>, which I also hate. At least I got to <style="Link">Buy Jewelery</style> at the airport.

attributes.label: The moon landing was fake
attributes.characterDialogue: She believes the moon landing is fake. Our horrible goverment has definitly set the whole thing up, they just wanted to brag with all of their expensive rockets. And those high up skyshots were definitly either computer generated or made with those wheather balons. When she is the richest person on earth she plans to take a look herself

attributes.label: The mount everest
attributes.characterDialogue: It's unbelievable but she never actually went. She is a lady of class and the hiking up would just be too physical. Especially because the enviroment will get really rough in those great heights.  They should build a Gondola up like Cozy Camping did

attributes.label: Great Heights
attributes.characterDialogue: Oh yes, I just love being up high. Maybe its the great view over everything. You know that's what my dream mansion is gonna look like. High up on a hill and appreciating all of the beautiful scenery. I'm starting to get why these greek people build their temples on this mountain above the cloud.
attributes.Clue/Filler: The feeling of being above the clouds is just different. It's beatiful honestly, you can really take in the view. I should also build my mansion high up

attributes.label: The horrible government
attributes.characterDialogue: This goverment? It is just horrible! Period. Firstly it completly discredits womanhood, by still allowing abortions. Like do they even realise how harmful abortions can be to woman. Like even offering me an abortion is basically saying "Your child should die and I will do that for you". Like do they think I'm not good enough to be a mother?  They also still haven't done anything against these climate activists, what if they destroy my painting with their tomato sauce? And even worse the are constantly wanting to steal my money and diguising it as taxes.
